RBAC:

Assign view (read-only)
oc adm policy add-role-to-user view user1 -n myproject

Assign edit (developer)
oc adm policy add-role-to-user edit student1 -n myproject

Assign admin (project admin)
oc adm policy add-role-to-user admin lead1 -n myproject

Assign cluster-admin (full access)
oc adm policy add-cluster-role-to-user cluster-admin venky

⚠️ Use carefully — full control

2. Create Custom Role (Fine-Grained Access)

Example: Only allow POD read access

--
Step 1: Create Role
cat <<EOF | oc apply -f -
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: Role
metadata:
  namespace: myproject
  name: pod-reader
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["pods","namespaces"]
  verbs: ["get", "list", "watch"]
EOF

Step 2: Bind Role to User
oc create rolebinding pod-reader-binding \
  --role=pod-reader \
  --user=student2 \
  -n myproject

--

🌍 3. Create Cluster-Level Custom Role

Example: Read nodes (cluster-wide)

--
cat <<EOF | oc apply -f -
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: ClusterRole
metadata:
  name: node-reader
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
  resources: ["nodes"]
  verbs: ["get", "list"]
EOF

Bind Cluster Role
oc create clusterrolebinding node-reader-binding \
  --clusterrole=node-reader \
  --user=student3
--

4. Remove Roles
Remove project role:
oc adm policy remove-role-from-user edit student1 -n myproject
Remove cluster role:
oc adm policy remove-cluster-role-from-user cluster-admin student1

5. Verify Access
Check roles in project:
oc get rolebindings -n myproject
Check user permissions:
oc auth can-i create pods --as=student1 -n myproject



